    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In that case, we can use a technique called \"Manacher's Algorithm\" to find the longest palindromic substring in linear time. This algorithm is specifically designed to find the longest palindromic substring in a string, and it's much faster than the previous approach.\n\nHere's the code using Manacher's Algorithm:\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    def manacher(s):\n        T = '#'.join('^{}$'.format(s))\n        n = len(T)\n        P = [0] * n\n        C = R = 0\n        for i in range(1, n-1):\n            P[i] = (R > i) and min(R - i, P[2*C - i])\n            while T[i + 1 + P[i]] == T[i - 1 - P[i]]:\n                P[i] += 1\n            if i + P[i] > R:\n                C, R = i, i + P[i]\n        max_len = 0\n        for i in range(n):\n            if P[i] > max_len:\n                max_len = P[i]\n        return max_len\n\n    return manacher(s) // 2\n``",
